{
  "chapter": {
    "children": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "1",
            "text": "So now, Job, I beg you, hear my speech;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "listen to all my words."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "2",
            "text": "See now, I have opened my mouth;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "my tongue has spoken in my mouth."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "3",
            "text": "My words come from the uprightness of my heart;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "my lips speak pure knowledge."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "4",
            "text": "The Spirit of God has made me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "the breath of the Almighty has given me life."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "5",
            "text": "If you can, answer me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "set your words in order before me and stand up."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "6",
            "text": "See, I am just as you are in God’s sight;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "I also have been formed out of the clay."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "7",
            "text": "See, terror of me will not make you afraid;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "neither will my pressure be heavy upon you."
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "8",
            "text": "You have certainly spoken in my hearing;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "I have heard the sound of your words saying,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "9",
            "text": "‘I am clean and without transgression;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "I am innocent, and there is no sin in me."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "10",
            "text": "See, God finds opportunities to attack me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "he regards me as his enemy."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "11",
            "text": "He puts my feet in stocks;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "he watches all my paths.’"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "12",
            "text": "See, in this you are not right—I will answer you,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "for God is greater than man."
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "13",
            "text": "Why do you struggle against him?"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "He does not account for any of his doings."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "14",
            "text": "For God speaks once—"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "yes, twice, though man does not notice it."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "15",
            "text": "In a dream, in a vision of the night,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "when deep sleep falls upon men,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "in slumber on the bed—"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "16",
            "text": "then God opens the ears of men,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "and frightens them with threats,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "17",
            "text": "in order to pull man back from his sinful purposes,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "and keep pride from him."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "18",
            "text": "God keeps man’s life back from the pit,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "his life from crossing over to death."
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "19",
            "text": "Man is punished also with pain on his bed,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "with constant agony in his bones,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "20",
            "text": "so that his life abhors food,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "and his soul abhors delicacies."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "21",
            "text": "His flesh is consumed away so that it cannot be seen;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "his bones, once not seen, now stick out."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "22",
            "text": "Indeed, his soul draws close to the pit,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "his life to those who wish to destroy it."
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "23",
            "text": "But if there is an angel who can be a mediator for him,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "one out of a thousand,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "to tell a man what is right for him,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "24",
            "text": "to be gracious to him and say,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "‘Save this person from going down to the pit;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "I have found a ransom for him.’"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "25",
            "text": "Then his flesh will become fresher than a child’s;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "it is restored to the days of his youth."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "26",
            "text": "He will pray to God, and God will be kind to him,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "so that he sees God’s face with joy."
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "God will give the person his triumph."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "27",
            "text": "Then that person will sing in front of other people and say,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "‘I sinned and perverted that which was right,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "but my sin was not punished."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "28",
            "text": "God has rescued my soul from going down into the pit;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "my life will continue to see light.’"
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "29",
            "text": "See, God does all these things with a person,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "twice, yes, even three times,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "30",
            "text": "to bring his soul back from the pit,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "so that he may be enlightened with the light of life."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "31",
            "text": "Pay attention, Job, and listen to me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "be silent and I will speak."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "32",
            "text": "If you have anything to say, answer me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "speak, for I wish to prove that you are in the right."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "33",
            "text": "If not, then listen to me;"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "remain silent, and I will teach you wisdom.”"
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      }
    ],
    "num": 33
  },
